  "texts": [
    "The proposed Dual Transformer model is applied only in scenarios involving polarity scores of related companies, since the input to the Enhancement Transformer is the polarity score.",
    "The MSE values of the Dual Transformer are highlighted in red if the Dual Transformer outperforms the other models, which is applied to both scenarios, \"with Polarity of Related Firms\" and \"with Fewer Related Firms\".Based on the results, the main findings are summarized as follows.",
    "First, the proposed Dual Transformer consistently outperforms other models across all companies for almost all the time when using features with the polarity of related firms.",
    "When using fewer related firms, the Dual Transformer achieves the lowest MSE values in some cases (Table 6 and 7), indicating that removing companies with minimal contributions to prediction is likely to enhance performance.",
    "However, in most cases, the Dual Transformer yields the best result with polarity of more related companies.In some instances, the Informer model and TFT with polarity scores as input exhibits comparative results with the Dual Transformer."
  ],
